MAP:DNA_REPAIR/MODULE:HR Homologous recombination is a type of genetic recombination and DNA repair pathwat in which genetic material is exchanged between two similar or identical strands of DNA. The process involves several steps of physical breaking, crossing over with sister chromatide to use it as a template for accurate gap re-feeling in the damaged strand and rejoining of DNA. This pathway does not introduce mutations in to the DNA. due to accurate repair of double-strand breaks during S-phase of the cell cycle when two sister chromatides are available.
